{"id": "EUVD-2025-20939", "enisaUuid": "b6026e25-2b92-3c41-b02a-3bde91288030", "description": "In the Linux kernel, the following vulnerability has been resolved:\n\ndrm/xe/vm: move xe_svm_init() earlier\n\nIn xe_vm_close_and_put() we need to be able to call xe_svm_fini(),\nhowever during vm creation we can call this on the error path, before\nhaving actually initialised the svm state, leading to various splats\nfollowed by a fatal NPD.\n\n(cherry picked from commit 4f296d77cf49fcb5f90b4674123ad7f3a0676165)", "datePublished": "2025-07-10T09:32:30", "dateUpdated": "2025-11-18T15:30:40", "baseScore": 0.0, "references": ["https://git.kernel.org/stable/c/f5e6a6a8aa46d44ec7a240766cf3b7dd077718b9", "https://git.kernel.org/stable/c/8cf8cde41ad01150afbd1327ad1942387787f7fd", "https://nvd.nist.gov/vuln/detail/CVE-2025-38309"], "aliases": ["CVE-2025-38309"], "assigner": "Linux", "epss": 0.02, "enisaIdProduct": [{"id": "02291b85-ac3b-3a55-a1f9-67e6abcdfb0a", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "patch: 6.15.3"}, {"id": "2db848dd-90c8-344f-a160-b903c0476765", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "patch: 6.16-rc1"}, {"id": "4c050ba5-562b-33c0-a4ff-e82dde7f9ba5", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "patch: 6.16"}, {"id": "75e7fe93-641a-39ce-b75f-294ae8dfa0fb", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "6fd979c2f33150e8261d87d2946f94f66f22ddaa <f5e6a6a8aa46d44ec7a240766cf3b7dd077718b9"}, {"id": "8a404d1c-af6f-392f-ac4a-10b54423924a", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "patch: 0"}, {"id": "a44b6ec5-ad57-3513-8d38-8ece561bfcb0", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "6.15"}, {"id": "ca76c1d9-99c5-3563-8c79-8999d69f7a58", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "6fd979c2f33150e8261d87d2946f94f66f22ddaa <8cf8cde41ad01150afbd1327ad1942387787f7fd"}], "enisaIdVendor": [{"id": "05935e09-4467-3299-8e66-f6824c2ebb48", "vendor": {"name": "Linux"}}], "isExploited": false}